Nairobi business associates of the Kenya Ports Authority were hosted to a luncheon at the Villa Rosa Kempinski Hotel on Thursday. The annual briefing brought together different stakeholders in the logistics, clearing and forwarding sector.Present at the luncheon were Transport CS James Macharia, PS Irungu Nyakera and Mining CS Dan Kazungu. Also in attendance were KPA managing director Catherine Mturi and acting National Oil chief executive Maryjane Mwangi.